to be a concert violinist.

76
00:05:50,635 --> 00:05:54,571
So I took a degree
in teaching.

77
00:05:54,639 --> 00:05:57,403
I bet you're
a great teacher.

78
00:05:57,475 --> 00:06:00,569
Well, I think I am.
Or I could...

79
00:06:00,645 --> 00:06:03,079
But every time I would
get started on something,

80
00:06:03,147 --> 00:06:05,081
Charles would be transferred.

81
00:06:05,149 --> 00:06:07,674
And then I had my kids,
and I took time out to raise them.

82
00:06:07,752 --> 00:06:10,016
Then by the time I wanted
to start teaching again,

83
00:06:10,087 --> 00:06:12,021
nobody would hire me
because...

84
00:06:12,089 --> 00:06:16,185
You know, Navy wife.
You can't count on her to stick around.

85
00:06:16,260 --> 00:06:21,357
So l-l-I decided what I would do
is start my own program.

86
00:06:21,432 --> 00:06:24,526
And Charles gave me
the money... to do that.

87
00:06:24,602 --> 00:06:29,369
- We were in Greece. I bought
50 violins at this little Greek shop.
- "Fifty"?

88
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:34,377
And I started the program
at this little private school and, uh...

89
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:39,807
- And then...
- And then your husband ran off
with your best friend.

90
00:06:39,884 --> 00:06:44,378
That's right. No, she was not
my best friend. She was <i>a friend.</i>

91
00:06:44,455 --> 00:06:47,618
So what are you gonna do? Just wrap
presents and wait till he comes back?

92
00:06:50,961 --> 00:06:52,895
