Can you do that?

905
00:58:04,260 --> 00:58:07,252
Roberta...

906
00:58:07,330 --> 00:58:09,855
Get out!

907
00:58:15,038 --> 00:58:17,063
All right.

908
00:58:17,140 --> 00:58:19,074
[Panting]

909
00:58:19,142 --> 00:58:21,076
All right.

910
00:58:22,645 --> 00:58:25,580
<i>[Footsteps Departing]</i>

911
00:58:41,231 --> 00:58:43,165
[Exhales]

912
00:59:24,908 --> 00:59:27,775
♪♪ ["Shave And A Haircut"]

913
00:59:27,844 --> 00:59:30,506
[Audience Laughs, Applauds]

914
00:59:30,580 --> 00:59:33,981
- Whew! That was great.
- [Audience Cheering]

915
00:59:34,050 --> 00:59:38,043
<i>[Applause, Cheering</i>
<i>Continue]</i>

916
00:59:38,121 --> 00:59:40,282
[Cheering, Whistling]

917
01:00:01,978 --> 01:00:04,071
<i>♪♪ [Stops, Shutters Click]</i>

918
01:00:04,147 --> 01:00:06,775
[Audience Murmuring, Softly]

919
01:00:12,889 --> 01:00:16,120
[Audience Chuckling]

920
01:00:22,799 --> 01:00:26,098
- [Exhales]
- <i>[Man] All right!</i>

921
01:00:26,169 --> 01:00:28,103
Bravo!

922
01:00:29,772 --> 01:00:33,230
[Audience Cheering]

923
01:00:33,309 --> 01:00:38,679
- All right!
- <i>[Applause, Cheers Continue]</i>

924
01:00:42,418 --> 01:00:46,445
- Yeah!
- <i>[Shutter Clicks]</i>

925
01:00:50,084 --> 01:00:55,021
- [Laughs]
- [Audience Cheering]

926
01:00:56,858 --> 01:01:01,192
<i>♪♪ [Salsa]</i>

927
01:01:06,067 --> 01:01:08,695
<i>[Janet] Children, today</i>
<i>is a very special day...</i>

928
01:01:08,769 --> 01:01:13,729
<i>because we're starting the tenth year</i>
<i>of the East Harlem Violin Program.</i>

929
01:01:13,808 --> 01:01:18,973
Now, some of you might know that I used
to teach just 50 kids at this school.

930
01:01:19,046 --> 01:01:21,412
But now I teach
150 kids...

931
01:01:21,449 --> 01:01:23,815
<i>at three different</i>
<i>East Harlem schools.</i>

932
01:01:24,983 --> 01:01:29,010
So many children want
to take this violin class
that we have to have a lottery.

933
01:01:29,087 --> 01:01:31,817
<i>[Janet]</i>
<i>Now this is a wonderful opportunity,</i>

934
01:01:31,889 --> 01:01:36,223
so I want you to talk to your
parents about whether or not
you would like to try this.

935
01:01:36,294 --> 01:01:40,822
My daughter took violin with Roberta
when she was your age.

936
01:01:40,898 --> 01:01:45,096
Now she's in high school, and she
still talks about how much she loved it.

937
01:01:45,169 --> 01:01:49,037
Janet and I
started this program...

938
01:01:49,107 --> 01:01:54,010
because we knew how much you kids
could benefit from it.

939
01:01:54,078 --> 01:01:58,242
<i>You should know, however,</i>
<i>the violin...</i>

940
01:01:58,316 --> 01:02:00,716
is a difficult instrument.

941
01:02:00,785 --> 01:02:02,719
So I...
What is it, Justin?

942
01:02:02,787 --> 01:02:05,312
- Who's that lady in the back?
- <i>[Janet] Oh, excuse me.</i>

943
01:02:05,390 --> 01:02:08,223
Yes, this is
Dorothea Von Hauften, and she...

944
01:02:08,292 --> 01:02:10,556
- What kind of name is that?
- <i>[Isabel] Justin, shh.</i>

945
01:02:10,628 --> 01:02:12,721
<i>[Janet] She's taking pictures</i>
<i>of Roberta's classes...</i>

946
01:02:12,797 --> 01:02:16,096
for a magazine article
on music education.

947
01:02:16,167 --> 01:02:18,761
- I want to be in a magazine.
- <i>[Isabel] First things first, Justin.</i>

948
01:02:18,836 --> 01:02:21,270
Roberta's going to explain to us
about the lottery.

949
01:02:21,339 --> 01:02:24,331
What we're gonna do is, you're going
to bring in your permission slips.

950
01:02:24,409 --> 01:02:26,900
<i>Have your parents sign them.</i>
<i>You bring them in.</i>

951
01:02:26,978 --> 01:02:29,378
I'm gonna take a hat.
I'm gonna close my eyes...

952
01:02:29,447 --> 01:02:34,180
and I'm gonna pick just 50 names
from each school...

953
01:02:34,252 --> 01:02:36,186
'cause there isn't enough room
for everybody else.

954
01:02:36,254 --> 01:02:40,623
<i>So, on Friday,</i>
<i>bring in the slips,</i>

955
01:02:40,692 --> 01:02:43,217
<i>and we will tell you</i>
<i>who gets to be...</i>

956
01:02:43,294 --> 01:02:47,196
- in the violin class.
- <i>[Roberta]</i>
<i>Yeah, but everybody gets a chance.</i>

957
01:02:47,265 --> 01:02:51,861
- Yes?
- I really, really hope
that I get in the class.

958
01:02:51,936 --> 01:02:55,201
- <i>[Adults Chuckle, Students Agree]</i>
- I really hope you do too.

959
01:02:55,406 --> 01:02:57,601
<i>♪♪ [Cello]</i>

960
01:03:27,705 --> 01:03:31,971
- ♪♪ [Stops]
Wait, Lex, what time is it?
- 2:20.

961
01:03:32,043 --> 01:03:36,912
- I got to go.
- <i>Nick, Lexi, how come you guys</i>
<i>don't play the violin?</i>

962
01:03:36,981 --> 01:03:40,849
We used to, but you know
how my mom is as a teacher?

963
01:03:40,918 --> 01:03:42,852
[Laughs]

964
01:03:42,920 --> 01:03:45,115
Picture her being your teacher
and your mother.

965
01:03:45,189 --> 01:03:47,953
- Oh, I'm sorry I'm so late.
- <i>[Lexi] Hi, Mom.</i>

966
01:03:48,025 --> 01:03:50,858
- <i>[Roberta] Hi, Rachel.</i>
- Hi.
- Hey, Allegra, come here.

967
01:03:50,928 --> 01:03:52,759
Nick, are you
finished practicing?

968
01:03:52,830 --> 01:03:54,923
- Yeah, I'm done.
- <i>[Roberta] Already?</i>

969
01:03:54,999 --> 01:03:58,127
- You hardly even practiced.
- <i>[Nick] What, are you</i>
<i>timing me with a stopwatch?</i>

970
01:03:58,202 --> 01:04:00,932
- Why don't you pick on Lexi
for a change?
- 'Cause I'm perfect.

971
01:04:01,005 --> 01:04:04,133
- 'Cause he's perfect.
- <i>[Hitting Lexi]</i>
<i>Yeah, but your head hurts, right?</i>

972
01:04:04,208 --> 01:04:07,177
- Have a good lesson, Rachel.
- Thanks.

973
01:04:07,245 --> 01:04:11,079
- Where are you going?
- I'm going to meet Lawrence,
play some basketball.

974
01:04:11,149 --> 01:04:13,583
- I'll be back in a couple of hours.
- Okay.

975
01:04:13,651 --> 01:04:18,748
<i>♪♪ [Violins]</i>

976
01:04:28,533 --> 01:04:30,694
Don't forget the vibrato.

977
01:04:33,871 --> 01:04:36,339
Dang,
I just can't get that right.

978
01:04:36,407 --> 01:04:38,341
Well, that's almost it.
You almost got it.

979
01:04:38,409 --> 01:04:40,570
Almost isn't good enough.

980
01:04:40,645 --> 01:04:46,208
Ooh, did I turn you
into such a perfectionist?

981
01:04:46,284 --> 01:04:48,445
No, I came that way.

982
01:04:48,519 --> 01:04:50,453
[Laughs]
That's what I thought.

983
01:04:50,521 --> 01:04:55,618
Well, just as long as you get it...
for your Juilliard audition.

984
01:04:55,693 --> 01:04:58,218
- [Turning Page]
- What?

985
01:04:58,296 --> 01:05:01,265
I've recommended you
for a gifted kids scholarship.

986
01:05:01,332 --> 01:05:03,266
Really?

987
01:05:03,334 --> 01:05:05,268
I think you can do it.

988
01:05:06,504 --> 01:05:09,564
And the next is...

989
01:05:09,640 --> 01:05:12,040
Shandra Wilson.

990
01:05:12,109 --> 01:05:15,806
- [Squealing]
- Yes!
- <i>[Roberta] Congratulations.</i>

991
01:05:15,880 --> 01:05:19,782
- All right, Shandra! Good for you.
- Congratulations, sweetie.

992
01:05:19,851 --> 01:05:25,380
- All right. Next is Justin Brady.
- Yes!

993
01:05:25,456 --> 01:05:27,481
- [Women Laughing]
- Yeah.

994
01:05:27,558 --> 01:05:29,583
- Yes!
- Here you go.

995
01:05:29,660 --> 01:05:32,595
- Next one is... Could be you.
- Look at this, Ramon.

996
01:05:32,663 --> 01:05:37,760
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>Vanessa Klein.</i>

997
01:05:37,835 --> 01:05:42,238
Vanessa, good for you, honey.
Wow, such a good class.

998
01:05:42,306 --> 01:05:43,933
<i>[Roberta]</i>
<i>And the very last one, okay?</i>

999
01:05:44,008 --> 01:05:48,377
- And that is Ramon Olivas.
- [Screaming]

1000
01:05:48,446 --> 01:05:53,349
All right, Ramon.
Good for you. Oh, my gosh.

1001
01:05:55,186 --> 01:06:01,022
[Children Squealing,
Chattering]

1002
01:06:01,092 --> 01:06:04,687
<i>[Chattering Continues]</i>

1003
01:06:04,762 --> 01:06:07,595
- Thank you!
- <i>[Woman] Yea!</i>

1004
01:06:07,665 --> 01:06:09,599
<i>[Child]</i>
<i>I got it!</i>

1005
01:06:09,667 --> 01:06:13,330
I got it!
[Cheers]

1006
01:06:15,072 --> 01:06:17,006
<i>[Chattering Continues]</i>

1007
01:06:29,854 --> 01:06:32,254
Does that really work,
the ticket thing?

1008
01:06:32,323 --> 01:06:34,257
- Oh. Oh, hello.
- Hello.

1009
01:06:34,325 --> 01:06:37,624
[Laughs] No, that doesn't work,
but I keep trying.

1010
01:06:37,695 --> 01:06:40,528
You know, maybe one day, the school
will give me a parking space.

1011
01:06:40,598 --> 01:06:42,589
- Oh.
- That would be nice.

1012
01:06:42,667 --> 01:06:46,159
- Here. Photographs.
- Oh!

1013
01:06:48,172 --> 01:06:53,439
Oh, no!
They're fantastic!

1014
01:06:53,511 --> 01:06:56,537
- <i>[Dorothea]</i>
<i>Those copies are for you.</i>
- <i>Oh, thank you so much!</i>

1015
01:06:56,614 --> 01:06:59,674
Oh, they're great!
Oh, can I pay you for them?

1016
01:06:59,750 --> 01:07:02,878
Oh, don't be silly. You'll need
your money for parking tickets.

1017
01:07:02,954 --> 01:07:06,481
Oh, thank you so much!
That's fantastic!

1018
01:07:06,557 --> 01:07:09,685
I think what you're doing
for these children... It's wonderful.

1019
01:07:09,760 --> 01:07:13,821
My husband's a violinist. He was very
impressed when I told him about you.

1020
01:07:13,898 --> 01:07:17,026
- Oh, really? What's his name?
- Arnold Steinhardt.

1021
01:07:18,602 --> 01:07:23,539
- Of the Guarneri String Quartet?
- Yeah. Oh, here.

1022
01:07:23,607 --> 01:07:26,508
Stay in touch. Let us know
when the kids have a concert.

1023
01:07:26,577 --> 01:07:28,875
I will, I will.
Oh, thank you.

1024
01:07:28,946 --> 01:07:32,313
Thank you so much.
That's really...

1025
01:07:32,383 --> 01:07:33,850
- Here.
- <i>That's... Oh, gosh.</i>

1026
01:07:33,918 --> 01:07:37,081
- Keys. Bye.
- Bye-bye.

1027
01:07:37,288 --> 01:07:40,519
Very good! Okay, now when you
take your violins home,

1028
01:07:40,591 --> 01:07:46,257
I'm gonna ask you to put your
music... Tape it up on the wall
directly in front of your nose.

1029
01:07:46,330 --> 01:07:50,232
'Cause you don't want to be bending over
like this, trying to read your music.

1030
01:07:50,301 --> 01:07:55,329
- <i>Your parents are gonna be</i>
<i>so excited to see you... play.</i>
- [Softly] Stop!

1031
01:07:57,942 --> 01:08:01,070
Yeah, okay.
Let's try it again.

1032
01:08:01,145 --> 01:08:04,376
<i>Ready?</i>
<i>And...</i>

1033
01:08:04,448 --> 01:08:07,508
<i>♪♪ [Violin, Off-Key]</i>

1034
01:08:07,585 --> 01:08:09,576
Ramon, how many cats
you killing back there?

1035
01:08:25,770 --> 01:08:27,704
Ready and...

1036
01:08:31,709 --> 01:08:36,271
Myesha, your stop sign
should be touching, honey.

1037
01:08:36,347 --> 01:08:39,646
<i>Don't let it wiggle around</i>
<i>like that.</i>

1038
01:08:39,717 --> 01:08:43,448
- Justin, you're on the wrong string.
- <i>[Door Opens, Closes]</i>

1039
01:08:43,521 --> 01:08:46,251
<i>Look at your feet.</i>
<i>All right, hold it, hold it, hold it.</i>

1040
01:08:46,323 --> 01:08:48,154
Wait a minute.
Wait a minute. What time...

1041
01:08:48,225 --> 01:08:52,457
- Vanessa, where is your violin?
- I forgot it.

1042
01:08:52,530 --> 01:08:54,521
Again?

1043
01:08:55,499 --> 01:08:57,262
This is...
Good-bye.

1044
01:08:57,334 --> 01:08:59,996
<i>Go on. Good-bye.</i>

1045
01:09:00,071 --> 01:09:02,505
I'm sorry, but, you know,
you may be dropped.

1046
01:09:02,573 --> 01:09:05,474
<i>Go!</i>
<i>[Clears Throat]</i>

1047
01:09:05,543 --> 01:09:09,274
Hey, Ramon, that's very much better.
I have to tell you, I'm very impressed.

1048
01:09:09,346 --> 01:09:13,578
- <i>[Door Opens, Closes]</i>
- That practicing is paying off.
Let me see your nails, Rosario.

1049
01:09:13,651 --> 01:09:17,815
See? You gotta keep these clipped.
And I'm looking at you too, Myesha.

1050
01:09:17,888 --> 01:09:20,288
- Everybody, I've told you...
- Drop dead, Justin!

1051
01:09:20,357 --> 01:09:22,848
- It was an accident.
- It was not!

1052
01:09:22,927 --> 01:09:25,862
Hey, Ramon, I don't like
that kind of talk in here!
You pick that stand up now.

1053
01:09:25,930 --> 01:09:27,761
You get the music.
Come on.

1054
01:09:27,832 --> 01:09:33,464
Listen to me, buddy.
We have a big concert coming up.
You're not gonna be in it maybe.

1055
01:09:33,537 --> 01:09:36,097
- <i>Is that what you want?</i>
- No.

1056
01:09:37,808 --> 01:09:42,609
- <i>[Girl Laughs] Ooh.</i>
- Nothing funny here.

1057
01:09:42,680 --> 01:09:45,376
- [Roberta Sighs]
- <i>[Man] Here you go, sweetheart.</i>
<i>Come on, I got it.</i>

1058
01:09:45,449 --> 01:09:47,474
- Good night.
- Bye-bye. Work hard.
- <i>Get inside.</i>

1059
01:09:47,551 --> 01:09:49,883
That a girl. We just got...
We're in a hurry, that's all.

1060
01:09:49,954 --> 01:09:51,888
- Mr. Klein?
- Yeah?

1061
01:09:51,956 --> 01:09:56,586
You know, I'm gonna have to drop
Vanessa from class if she keeps
forgetting her violin.

1062
01:09:58,062 --> 01:10:00,155
Hey, look...

1063
01:10:00,231 --> 01:10:03,598
she's going back and forth
between houses.

1064
01:10:03,667 --> 01:10:06,067
My wife and I split up.

1065
01:10:07,905 --> 01:10:10,738
Oh. I'm sorry.

1066
01:10:10,808 --> 01:10:13,242
Vanessa, why don't you write down
for your mom and dad...

1067
01:10:14,441 --> 01:10:16,432
<i>which days are violin days,</i>
<i>okay?</i>

1068
01:10:17,911 --> 01:10:19,845
[Pats Mr. Klein's Shoulder]

1069
01:10:26,153 --> 01:10:27,950
Relax your two, Simon.
Good.

1070
01:10:32,219 --> 01:10:34,312
Kenny, your stop sign should be up.
Up, up, up, up. That's better.

1071
01:10:34,387 --> 01:10:37,845
<i>Stephanie, you look like</i>
<i>you never had a violin lesson</i>
<i>with me in your entire life!</i>

1072
01:10:40,560 --> 01:10:42,494
Oh, Carlos.
Where's your violin?

1073
01:10:42,562 --> 01:10:46,054
- Um... it's coming.
- What's it, walking here by itself?

1074
01:10:46,133 --> 01:10:49,569
- <i>[Girl] I'm coming!</i>
- Thank you.

1075
01:10:49,636 --> 01:10:53,504
- Your buddies giving you a hard time?
- Look, it's just not cool.

1076
01:10:53,573 --> 01:10:56,406
- <i>You wouldn't understand.</i>
- You want your sister to carry
your violin, that's fine.

1077
01:10:56,476 --> 01:10:59,570
But is she practicing
for you too? Because that's
the way it sounds to me lately.

1078
01:10:59,646 --> 01:11:01,580
- I've been busy.
- I don't want to hear it.

1079
01:11:01,648 --> 01:11:03,616
Get here on time and commit to
this class or I don't want you in here.

1080
01:11:03,683 --> 01:11:05,844
<i>You understand me?</i>
<i>Go.</i>

1081
01:11:05,919 --> 01:11:10,720
<i>Go.</i>

1082
01:11:16,496 --> 01:11:19,090
You're a good violinist,
Carlos,

1083
01:11:19,166 --> 01:11:22,260
but it is definitely not cool
to waste your talent.

1084
01:11:22,335 --> 01:11:25,236
- <i>Okay?</i>
- Yeah.

1085
01:11:25,305 --> 01:11:28,934
<i>So, let's do it again.</i>
<i>Perfect this time.</i>

1086
01:11:29,142 --> 01:11:31,337
[Sighs]

1087
01:11:31,411 --> 01:11:33,345
Hi.

1088
01:11:36,783 --> 01:11:38,717
Hey...

1089
01:11:46,927 --> 01:11:48,588
What happened?

1090
01:11:54,134 --> 01:11:56,068
[Sighs]

1091
01:11:56,136 --> 01:12:01,506
- I guess you've all heard
the bad news about Justin.
- I didn't hear.

1092
01:12:01,575 --> 01:12:04,339
<i>There was a drive-by</i>
<i>shooting by his house,</i>

1093
01:12:04,411 --> 01:12:06,606
and he got shot by accident
and he died.

1094
01:12:11,051 --> 01:12:12,916
[Sighs]

1095
01:12:15,255 --> 01:12:18,122
Would anybody like
to talk about this now?

1096
01:12:30,904 --> 01:12:32,838
Ramon?

1097
01:12:32,906 --> 01:12:36,842
I think we should
just play violin.

1098
01:12:46,119 --> 01:12:48,110
<i>♪♪ [Violin]</i>

1099
01:12:48,188 --> 01:12:50,122
<i>[Knocking]</i>

1100
01:12:57,430 --> 01:12:59,830
<i>[Knocking Continues]</i>

1101
01:13:01,468 --> 01:13:06,701
- Roberta, come in.
- I just wanted to stop
by and check on Ramon.

1102
01:13:06,773 --> 01:13:11,176
- Why?
- Didn't he tell you what happened
at school today?

1103
01:13:18,385 --> 01:13:20,319
♪♪ [Violin]

1104
01:13:24,658 --> 01:13:30,062
- Hey, Roberta wants
to talk to you, okay?
- Okay.

1105
01:13:43,543 --> 01:13:46,341
- Did that sound okay?
- That sounded very good.

1106
01:13:46,413 --> 01:13:49,974
[Moves Chair Closer]
Very good.

1107
01:13:53,420 --> 01:13:55,354
I've been thinking
about Justin.

1108
01:13:55,422 --> 01:13:57,356
[Sighs]

1109
01:13:57,424 --> 01:14:01,053
Remember how mad I was
at him the last time I saw him?

1110
01:14:01,127 --> 01:14:04,619
Yeah. You got
really strict with him.

1111
01:14:04,698 --> 01:14:09,431
Yeah, but, you know, it wasn't
always easy to be nice to him.

1112
01:14:09,502 --> 01:14:14,201
You think Justin's
in heaven or hell?

1113
01:14:14,274 --> 01:14:16,105
Heaven.

1114
01:14:19,279 --> 01:14:21,372
I told him to drop dead.

1115
01:14:21,448 --> 01:14:26,385
Well, Justin didn't die
because you said that.

1116
01:14:26,453 --> 01:14:29,479
- <i>I promise.</i>
- How would you know?

1117
01:14:29,556 --> 01:14:35,153
Well, I don't think
you're that powerful. You know?

1118
01:14:35,228 --> 01:14:37,389
<i>If you had such powers,</i>

1119
01:14:37,464 --> 01:14:40,763
<i>just imagine what kind of</i>
<i>a violinist you'd be by now.</i>

1120
01:14:40,834 --> 01:14:45,237
- Yeah, I'd be better than you.
- [Laughing]

1121
01:14:47,907 --> 01:14:52,207
<i>[Sighing]</i>

1122
01:14:52,278 --> 01:14:54,212
It's okay to cry.

1123
01:14:55,482 --> 01:14:57,677
Not for a man.

1124
01:14:57,751 --> 01:15:00,515
My boys still cry,

1125
01:15:00,587 --> 01:15:04,648
and they're big, strong
young men <i>now:</i>

1126
01:15:04,724 --> 01:15:07,522
And I'll bet Justin's
daddy cried.

1127
01:15:07,594 --> 01:15:12,361
[Sniffs]

1128
01:15:12,432 --> 01:15:16,732
[Crying]

1129
01:15:16,803 --> 01:15:18,737
[Softly]
It's okay.

1130
01:15:21,708 --> 01:15:24,074
[Muttering]

1131
01:15:24,144 --> 01:15:27,773
[Continues Muttering]

1132
01:15:31,284 --> 01:15:33,582
What's this?

1133
01:15:33,653 --> 01:15:35,587
[Clears Throat]

1134
01:15:37,791 --> 01:15:40,726
Oh. What is all this?

1135
01:15:50,937 --> 01:15:53,804
What is this?

1136
01:15:53,873 --> 01:15:56,671
[Reading, Softly]

1137
01:15:59,412 --> 01:16:01,880
I...

1138
01:16:03,917 --> 01:16:06,977
Nick! Lexi!
You come down here right now!

1139
01:16:10,256 --> 01:16:12,349
<i>[Nick]</i>
<i>Mom, we were just trying to help.</i>

1140
01:16:14,294 --> 01:16:16,922
[Softly]
This is so humiliating.

1141
01:16:16,996 --> 01:16:19,328
No one even knows
it's you.

1142
01:16:19,399 --> 01:16:21,959
I mean, you don't even have to
read them, if you don't want to.

1143
01:16:22,035 --> 01:16:24,526
- [Sighs]
- Although, look, obviously,

1144
01:16:24,604 --> 01:16:26,936
a lot of guys are interested
in dating you.

1145
01:16:27,006 --> 01:16:31,272
No, a lot of guys are interested
in dating you and Lexi.

1146
01:16:33,413 --> 01:16:35,847
What did you say
about me anyway?

1147
01:16:35,915 --> 01:16:38,907
[Laughs]
Beautiful musician,

1148
01:16:38,985 --> 01:16:41,249
late thirties,
tired of playing solo...

1149
01:16:41,321 --> 01:16:45,587
Seeks a healthy, stable, attractive man
who's not afraid of a duet...

1150
01:16:45,658 --> 01:16:47,956
- <i>with a strong, independent woman.</i>
- [Laughing]

1151
01:16:48,027 --> 01:16:50,359
My violin playing
will feed your soul.

1152
01:16:50,430 --> 01:16:52,455
<i>And my lasagna will be music</i>
<i>to your palette.</i>

1153
01:16:52,532 --> 01:16:54,466
Oh, my God!

1154
01:16:54,534 --> 01:16:57,503
Did you catch
all the music metaphors?

1155
01:16:57,570 --> 01:17:00,835
Oh, no. Listen, don't you think
it's a little weird...

1156
01:17:00,907 --> 01:17:02,932
that you're trying
to get your mother a date?

1157
01:17:03,009 --> 01:17:05,307
And don't hit him again
or I'll smack you.

1158
01:17:05,378 --> 01:17:08,279
Don't you think it's a little weird that
you're not even interested in dating?

1159
01:17:08,348 --> 01:17:12,148
Look, even if I were
interested in dating,

1160
01:17:12,218 --> 01:17:15,153
which... which I'm not,

1161
01:17:15,221 --> 01:17:18,520
I don't have time to do that,
and, besides, you know,

1162
01:17:18,591 --> 01:17:20,889
<i>I have my teaching...</i>
<i>which I love.</i>

1163
01:17:22,795 --> 01:17:25,525
I have you...
and you.

1164
01:17:27,600 --> 01:17:29,568
That's all I need.

1165
01:17:32,438 --> 01:17:35,635
- <i>[Footsteps Departing]</i>
- I really thought she'd
like the music metaphors.

1166
01:17:36,709 --> 01:17:38,734
She said don't hit me.

1167
01:17:44,717 --> 01:17:48,084
[Groans]
God.

1168
01:17:56,129 --> 01:17:59,496
"Dan Paxton."
[Chuckles]

1169
01:18:01,034 --> 01:18:02,968
[Laughing]

1170
01:18:05,572 --> 01:18:08,405
That's good.
That's good.

1171
01:18:08,608 --> 01:18:11,907
♪♪ [Both Playing]

1172
01:18:11,978 --> 01:18:13,536
- <i>♪♪ [Piano, Cello Continue]</i>
- You're flat, Nick.

1173
01:18:13,613 --> 01:18:16,104
- I'm not flat, Mom.
- Sounds flat to me.

1174
01:18:16,182 --> 01:18:18,173
Play the violin.
I'll take care of the cello, okay?

1175
01:18:24,290 --> 01:18:26,520
♪♪ [Playing]
So, you nervous, Mom?

1176
01:18:26,593 --> 01:18:28,925
No.

1177
01:18:30,830 --> 01:18:32,457
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>
- [Barks]

1178
01:18:37,704 --> 01:18:42,300
I'm... I'm just...
I'll be right back. I just...

1179
01:18:42,375 --> 01:18:44,309
Let him in.

1180
01:18:51,517 --> 01:18:55,647
Hi. I'm Dan Paxton.

1181
01:18:55,722 --> 01:18:57,656
- Is this the right place?
- Yeah.

1182
01:18:57,724 --> 01:18:59,692
- Roberta, right?
- Yeah. I'm her son, Lexi.

1183
01:18:59,759 --> 01:19:04,093
- Oh, hi, Lexi. Nice to meet you.
- You can go in the living room.

1184
01:19:04,163 --> 01:19:07,496
[Exhaling]

1185
01:19:07,567 --> 01:19:09,762
- Hi.
- Nick.

1186
01:19:09,836 --> 01:19:11,963
- Uh, Dan.
- Dan, nice to meet you.

1187
01:19:12,038 --> 01:19:15,974
- This is Allegra and...
- Hi. Oh, hey.

1188
01:19:16,042 --> 01:19:18,977
She should be...
She should be out in a minute.

1189
01:19:20,246 --> 01:19:22,180
<i>[Roberta Closes Door]</i>
<i>Hi.</i>

1190
01:19:26,386 --> 01:19:28,752
- Dan?
- Yeah.

1191
01:19:28,821 --> 01:19:31,813
- Hi, I'm Roberta.
- Wow. An honest woman.

1192
01:19:31,891 --> 01:19:34,189
- "Honest"?
- Your ad.

1193
01:19:34,260 --> 01:19:37,491
You said you were a beautiful woman,
and you were telling the truth.

1194
01:19:39,198 --> 01:19:42,065
Oh.
[Giggles]

1195
01:19:43,703 --> 01:19:47,969
- We should probably take off... soon.
- Okay, all right.

1196
01:19:48,041 --> 01:19:49,975
I'll get my bag.

1197
01:19:53,413 --> 01:19:56,280
Make sure you're home
by midnight, young lady.

1198
01:19:59,052 --> 01:20:02,818
- [Laughing] He's like six four.
- I know.

1199
01:20:02,889 --> 01:20:05,323
<i>[Lexi]</i>
<i>To the right. To the right.</i>

1200
01:20:05,391 --> 01:20:08,121
<i>[Video Game Continues]</i>

1201
01:20:08,194 --> 01:20:10,662
- <i>[Brakes Squeaking]</i>
- That's the car. They're here.

1202
01:20:10,730 --> 01:20:13,722
- <i>All right.</i>
- Oh, Mommy's late.

1203
01:20:13,800 --> 01:20:15,825
- What time is it anyway?
- 12:30.

1204
01:20:15,902 --> 01:20:18,234
- <i>That's promising.</i>
- <i>Ten bucks says he tries to kiss her.</i>

1205
01:20:18,304 --> 01:20:21,637
That's a no-brainer. Of course,
he'll try. The real question
is whether she lets him.

1206
01:20:21,708 --> 01:20:24,677
- Okay, ten bucks she lets him.
- You're on.

1207
01:20:24,744 --> 01:20:27,269
Well, I had a good time
tonight.

1208
01:20:27,347 --> 01:20:30,373
Yeah, I did too.
I, uh...

1209
01:20:32,318 --> 01:20:34,252
I have a confession
to make though.

1210
01:20:34,320 --> 01:20:36,914
Uh...
[Clears Throat, Laughs]

1211
01:20:36,989 --> 01:20:38,980
Uh, I've...

1212
01:20:39,058 --> 01:20:41,720
I've never answered
an ad before.

1213
01:20:41,794 --> 01:20:45,787
Uh, I lost a poker bet.

1214
01:20:45,865 --> 01:20:49,926
- [Laughing]
- [Laughing] No.

1215
01:20:50,002 --> 01:20:53,335
But I'm glad I did.
But I... [Laughs]

1216
01:20:53,406 --> 01:20:56,637
I have a little confession
myself.

1217
01:20:56,709 --> 01:21:02,011
[Laughing]
My boys placed the ad behind my back.

1218
01:21:02,081 --> 01:21:04,345
- You're kidding.
- <i>[Laughing] No.</i>

1219
01:21:04,417 --> 01:21:06,351
- [Laughing] I had a great time.
- <i>No. Really?</i>

1220
01:21:06,419 --> 01:21:09,877
Yeah, they did this.
They're so worried I have no...

1221
01:21:09,956 --> 01:21:12,584
social life.

1222
01:21:12,658 --> 01:21:15,593
- Ten dollars.
- No way, man. She ain't gonna kiss him.

1223
01:21:15,661 --> 01:21:17,595
- Just watch.
- Shut up.

1224
01:21:26,105 --> 01:21:28,539
Dan, I just...
I want to tell...

1225
01:21:28,608 --> 01:21:33,739
I went along with this because
it's been a while for me.

1226
01:21:33,813 --> 01:21:35,747
<i>It's been quite a while.</i>

1227
01:21:35,815 --> 01:21:38,215
But, um, I'm not sure...

1228
01:21:38,284 --> 01:21:41,947
I really want to get involved
with anybody just yet.

1229
01:21:42,021 --> 01:21:45,115
Does this mean
I don't get any lasagna?

1230
01:21:45,191 --> 01:21:48,991
- [Laughing] Oh, yeah.
- [Laughing]

1231
01:21:49,061 --> 01:21:51,928
<i>Bye.</i>

1232
01:21:51,998 --> 01:21:53,932
[Gasps, Laughing]
Oh, my God!

1233
01:21:54,000 --> 01:21:57,697
- Jesus, what are you guys doing up?
- Sorry.

1234
01:21:57,770 --> 01:21:59,704
- Why, is it late?
- [Laughing]

1235
01:21:59,772 --> 01:22:03,674
- How was it, Mom?
- It was nice, you know.

1236
01:22:03,743 --> 01:22:05,677
- "Nice"?
- Yeah.

1237
01:22:05,745 --> 01:22:07,736
[Nick] What, as in like
"Let's just be friends" nice?

1238
01:22:07,814 --> 01:22:10,908
Well, you know,
I don't know.

1239
01:22:10,983 --> 01:22:14,043
But we'll see.

1240
01:22:14,120 --> 01:22:16,782
- You know, there's a lot more letters.
- Good night, Nick.

1241
01:22:16,856 --> 01:22:18,790
- Good night, Mom.
- Good night, baby. [Kisses Lexi]

1242
01:22:18,858 --> 01:22:20,951
Good night, Mom.

1243
01:22:21,027 --> 01:22:22,961
That's right.
Pay up.

1244
01:22:23,029 --> 01:22:25,827
Mom, could you
loan me ten dollars?

1245
01:22:33,840 --> 01:22:36,741
<i>[Door Opens, Closes]</i>

1246
01:22:36,809 --> 01:22:40,176
[Panting]
Hi. Kids, I'm sorry I'm late.

1247
01:22:40,246 --> 01:22:44,546
I got stuck over at C.P.E. 2.

1248
01:22:44,617 --> 01:22:47,745
[Panting]
Where are your violins?

1249
01:22:56,028 --> 01:22:59,520
- What's the matter?
- We heard you got fired.

1250
01:22:59,599 --> 01:23:03,228
[Scoffs]
You what?

1251
01:23:05,271 --> 01:23:07,865
<i>[Ramon]</i>
<i>They don't want music anymore.</i>

1252
01:23:16,148 --> 01:23:18,082
Is it true?

1253
01:23:18,150 --> 01:23:21,244
- Come into the office, Roberta.
- It's true? You're firing me?

1254
01:23:21,320 --> 01:23:24,187
It wasn't me, Roberta.
The Board of Ed cut the budget.

1255
01:23:24,257 --> 01:23:26,487
The district had to comply.

1256
01:23:26,559 --> 01:23:30,154
As of the end of this term,
the violin program has been excessed.

1257
01:23:30,229 --> 01:23:32,254
"Excessed"?

1258
01:23:32,331 --> 01:23:35,266
They specifically said
that my violin program has to go?

1259
01:23:35,334 --> 01:23:38,861
They slashed the budget! Music and
art programs got hit the worst.

1260
01:23:38,938 --> 01:23:41,270
- Yeah, what about Dennis's classes?
- Uh, I'm tenured, Roberta.

1261
01:23:41,340 --> 01:23:43,274
Yeah. When was this
decided anyway?

1262
01:23:43,342 --> 01:23:46,072
Things happened very quickly.
I wanted to tell you myself.

1263
01:23:46,145 --> 01:23:49,774
- I can't believe this is happening!
- Why not? You are a sub.

1264
01:23:49,849 --> 01:23:53,785
- <i>Your position has never been permanent.</i>
- <i>Hey, Dennis, just smile!</i>

1265
01:23:53,853 --> 01:23:56,253
- This is the happiest day
of your life, isn't it?
- Come into the office.

1266
01:23:56,322 --> 01:23:58,950
You are not helping.

1267
01:24:00,326 --> 01:24:02,260
- [Sighs]
- Come on.

1268
01:24:05,164 --> 01:24:08,429
- There must be some way
that we can fight this.
- Fight it with what?

1269
01:24:08,501 --> 01:24:12,028
I don't have any other extra programs
I can give them instead.

1270
01:24:12,104 --> 01:24:15,403
[Scoffing]
I see. I see.

1271
01:24:15,474 --> 01:24:18,966
After ten years, after 1,400 kids
have learned the violin,

1272
01:24:19,045 --> 01:24:20,979
this is just
an "extra program."

1273
01:24:21,047 --> 01:24:22,981
You know I don't
feel that way,

1274
01:24:23,049 --> 01:24:25,779
and you know <i>damn well</i> I've been
standing by you all these years!

1275
01:24:25,851 --> 01:24:28,081
You think I haven't noticed
what you've done for these kids?

1276
01:24:28,154 --> 01:24:30,987
- Then do something!
- I have been on this phone
for the past three days...

1277
01:24:31,057 --> 01:24:33,218
trying to <i>do</i> something!

1278
01:24:33,292 --> 01:24:36,159
They're sick of hearing my voice!
Believe me...

1279
01:24:36,228 --> 01:24:39,254
there are other people around here
I would much rather get rid of,

1280
01:24:39,332 --> 01:24:45,168
but as far as the board is concerned,
violin classes are not a priority!

1281
01:24:45,237 --> 01:24:48,229
I don't have
the power here, Roberta.

1282
01:24:50,710 --> 01:24:52,200
I am so sorry.

1283
01:24:54,080 --> 01:24:56,014
<i>[Door Closes]</i>

1284
01:25:35,788 --> 01:25:38,154
♪♪ [Playing]

1285
01:26:15,728 --> 01:26:18,822
<i>[Applause, Cheering]</i>

1286
01:26:18,898 --> 01:26:22,163
<i>[Applause, Cheering</i>
<i>Continue]</i>

1287
01:26:25,905 --> 01:26:29,432
<i>[Applause, Cheering</i>
<i>Continue]</i>

1288
01:26:29,508 --> 01:26:32,944
[Continues Cheering]

1289
01:26:39,085 --> 01:26:41,747
- <i>[Roberta] Please sit.</i>
- [Applause Dies Down]

1290
01:26:45,524 --> 01:26:48,721
This beautiful concert
that you just heard...

1291
01:26:50,463 --> 01:26:52,761
could be
the very last concert...

1292
01:26:52,832 --> 01:26:55,858
- <i>of the East Harlem Violin Program.</i>
- [Audience Murmuring]

1293
01:26:55,935 --> 01:27:00,463
<i>The Board of Ed and the district</i>
<i>superintendent think that music...</i>

1294
01:27:00,539 --> 01:27:03,940
isn't important
for our kids.

1295
01:27:04,009 --> 01:27:07,740
- [Murmuring]
- <i>[Roberta] But they are wrong,</i>

1296
01:27:07,813 --> 01:27:11,305
- and they're gonna get a big fight.
- <i>[Applause, Cheering]</i>

1297
01:27:11,383 --> 01:27:13,749
[Continues Cheering]

1298
01:27:13,819 --> 01:27:15,878
<i>[Applause, Cheering</i>
<i>Continue]</i>

1299
01:27:21,727 --> 01:27:25,561
[Cheering]

1300
01:27:25,631 --> 01:27:29,397
<i>[Cheering Continues]</i>

1301
01:27:29,468 --> 01:27:33,768
[Continues Cheering]

1302
01:27:34,039 --> 01:27:36,098
<i>[Assunta]</i>
<i>Why do the parents have to meet here?</i>

1303
01:27:36,175 --> 01:27:38,973
- <i>You should be using the vacuum</i>
<i>cleaner, by the way. I got it.</i>
- <i>[Doorbell Rings]</i>

1304
01:27:39,044 --> 01:27:41,808
- <i>[Allegra Barking]</i>
- Oh, God, somebody's early.

1305
01:27:43,549 --> 01:27:48,316
- Hello, Assunta. How are you?
- Well, I'd be a lot better...

1306
01:27:48,387 --> 01:27:51,356
- if my daughter had a job next year.
- Well, so would I.

1307
01:27:51,423 --> 01:27:53,948
- Ma.
- [Groans]
Sorry I'm early, but, um...

1308
01:27:54,026 --> 01:27:57,291
I figured we'd need
a little extra time to set up.

1309
01:27:57,363 --> 01:28:01,026
Beware of Greeks
bearing you-know-what.

1310
01:28:01,100 --> 01:28:03,694
Mommy, will you mind taking Allegra
for a walk right now please?

1311
01:28:03,769 --> 01:28:06,795
- <i>You are having a meeting here tonight,</i>
<i>right? Parents and teachers?</i>
- Yes.

1312
01:28:06,872 --> 01:28:08,965
- Get down, get down.
- <i>[Assunta]</i>
<i>Come on, Allegra. Let's go.</i>

1313
01:28:09,041 --> 01:28:12,204
- <i>[Janet] Take it from me,</i>
- Good-bye.

1314
01:28:12,278 --> 01:28:14,303
if you want to get parents to help you
with something, you got to feed them.

1315
01:28:14,380 --> 01:28:17,178
- Do you have a cutting board for these?
- <i>[Door Closes]</i>

1316
01:28:17,249 --> 01:28:21,447
[Unpacking Bags] And if you think
parents are bad, teachers are worse.

1317
01:28:21,520 --> 01:28:23,545
Believe me, I know.
I was a teacher.

1318
01:28:23,622 --> 01:28:26,352
That's why I brought snacks.

1319
01:28:26,425 --> 01:28:29,724
- Wow.
- Gets them every time. [Chuckles]

1320
01:28:29,795 --> 01:28:33,231
[Continues Unpacking Bags]
Uh, you didn't expect me
to bring homemade, did you?

1321
01:28:33,299 --> 01:28:37,258
- No, I didn't...
- Good, because my husband begs me
to stay out of the kitchen.

1322
01:28:41,574 --> 01:28:45,533
- I didn't expect you to be here at all.
- Why not?

1323
01:28:46,846 --> 01:28:48,780
We got to figure out a way
to fight this.

1324
01:28:49,882 --> 01:28:51,941
And after ten years,
I don't know,

1325
01:28:52,017 --> 01:28:55,316
I just can't imagine walking down
those hallways and not hearing that...

1326
01:28:55,387 --> 01:28:58,185
off-key, nails-on-blackboard
violin music.

1327
01:28:58,257 --> 01:29:00,748
[Laughing]

1328
01:29:00,826 --> 01:29:02,953
Thank you.

1329
01:29:05,264 --> 01:29:10,327
- Ma. Ma, get some...
- I'll tell you this.

1330
01:29:10,402 --> 01:29:12,336
If this was
a downtown problem,

1331
01:29:12,404 --> 01:29:14,269
- they would take care of it tomorrow.
- [Guests Agreeing]

1332
01:29:14,340 --> 01:29:17,036
Absolutely right.

1333
01:29:17,109 --> 01:29:18,906
They don't realize how much
this program helps our kids.

1334
01:29:18,978 --> 01:29:21,913
Simon is our third child
to study with Roberta.

1335
01:29:21,981 --> 01:29:24,575
<i>james is premed.</i>
<i>April is valedictorian.</i>

1336
01:29:24,650 --> 01:29:27,619
- Now that says something.
- <i>[Woman] Nobody knows that.</i>

1337
01:29:27,686 --> 01:29:31,087
<i>We should inundate</i>
<i>the board and the district</i>
<i>with letters. I mean, flood them.</i>

1338
01:29:31,156 --> 01:29:33,852
It doesn't matter how many letters you
send them. It's just not in the budget.

1339
01:29:33,926 --> 01:29:36,554
- What if we raise the money ourselves?
- Oh, they wouldn't object.

1340
01:29:36,629 --> 01:29:39,097
[Dorothea]
What if you did a benefit concert?

1341
01:29:39,164 --> 01:29:42,930
<i>We could raise a batch of money</i>
<i>from the ticket sales,</i>

1342
01:29:43,002 --> 01:29:46,733
and the concert itself could
be great publicity for the program.

1343
01:29:46,805 --> 01:29:50,798
It can't just be me
and the kids, I don't think,
not if you're gonna charge money.

1344
01:29:50,876 --> 01:29:53,344
Perhaps I could persuade Arnold
to play with you and the kids.

1345
01:29:53,412 --> 01:29:57,872
- <i>[Guests Gasp]</i>
- <i>And, well, maybe he can get</i>
<i>another violinist too.</i>

1346
01:29:57,950 --> 01:29:59,884
Itzhak Perlman, perhaps.

1347
01:29:59,952 --> 01:30:02,785
Itzhak Perlman?
Arnold and... Arnold would do this?

1348
01:30:02,855 --> 01:30:04,880
Itzhak Perlman?
[Giggling]

1349
01:30:04,957 --> 01:30:06,948
And Arnold... Would they
do this, though?

1350
01:30:07,026 --> 01:30:09,051
<i>Yes, Arnold and Itzhak</i>
<i>are very good friends.</i>

1351
01:30:09,128 --> 01:30:11,062
- <i>[Roberta]</i>
<i>Seriously, you think they would?</i>
- Yes, yes.

1352
01:30:11,130 --> 01:30:15,499
And we could rent a place like the
92nd Street "Y." It's perfect for this.

1353
01:30:15,567 --> 01:30:19,333
- It seats about 900 people.
- Nine hundred would be more than enough.

1354
01:30:19,405 --> 01:30:23,000
And if we charge between
$50 and $100 a ticket, then...

1355
01:30:23,075 --> 01:30:25,407
That could raise you enough
to reinstate your program for a year.

1356
01:30:25,477 --> 01:30:27,604
- <i>[Guests Chattering]</i>
- That's a very... That's a great idea.

1357
01:30:27,680 --> 01:30:30,342
- That's a lot of money, Roberta.
- It'll be fun.

1358
01:30:30,416 --> 01:30:33,317
- <i>[Doorbell Rings, Guests Chattering]</i>
- If you can get us the fellows.

1359
01:30:33,385 --> 01:30:37,788
Beg him. Do whatever
you need to do.

1360
01:30:37,856 --> 01:30:42,793
- Hi.
- Well, I have some good news
and some great news.

1361
01:30:42,861 --> 01:30:45,352
- [Gasps]
- We're in five different papers.

1362
01:30:45,431 --> 01:30:47,695
<i>[Guests Chattering]</i>

1363
01:30:47,766 --> 01:30:52,430
Oh, my... Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
[Screams]

1364
01:30:52,504 --> 01:30:55,996
- [Whooping]
- [Chattering]

1365
01:30:56,075 --> 01:31:01,570
<i>[Chattering Continues]</i>

1366
01:31:09,188 --> 01:31:12,055
Itzhak, it's Arnold.

1367
01:31:12,124 --> 01:31:13,989
You know,
the other fiddler.

1368
01:31:14,059 --> 01:31:16,220
I have something
to propose to you.

1369
01:31:17,796 --> 01:31:19,730
[Chattering]

1370
01:31:19,798 --> 01:31:22,358
<i>♪ Let's break all the rules ♪

1371
01:31:22,434 --> 01:31:24,902
<i>♪ Come on, baby</i>
<i>Me and you ♪

1372
01:31:28,540 --> 01:31:31,373
- Thank you.
- [Merchant] Okay, good luck.

1373
01:31:37,282 --> 01:31:39,546
<i>♪ Let's break all the rules ♪

1374
01:31:39,618 --> 01:31:41,745
<i>♪ Come on, baby</i>
<i>Me and you ♪

1375
01:31:45,691 --> 01:31:47,818
<i>♪♪ [Spanish]</i>

1376
01:31:49,294 --> 01:31:51,592
<i>♪♪ [Spanish]</i>

1377
01:31:55,000 --> 01:31:56,934
[Talking, Laughing]

1378
01:32:00,105 --> 01:32:02,733
Hey!
[Yells]

1379
01:32:02,808 --> 01:32:06,972
Everybody, listen to me.
Pay attention. Fall in.

1380
01:32:07,046 --> 01:32:10,277
<i>You people</i>
<i>are my very best...</i>

1381
01:32:10,349 --> 01:32:13,250
beginning and advanced
violin students,

1382
01:32:13,318 --> 01:32:16,913
and that's why you have been chosen
to be in the Fiddlefest.

1383
01:32:16,989 --> 01:32:21,585
Because I trust that
you can handle this pressure.

1384
01:32:21,660 --> 01:32:25,289
This is gonna be a lot of work,
a lot, a lot of work!

1385
01:32:25,364 --> 01:32:27,525
<i>People have already</i>
<i>bought tickets to this thing,</i>

1386
01:32:27,599 --> 01:32:29,863
<i>and we are not gonna be here</i>
<i>in the fall if, you know,</i>

1387
01:32:29,935 --> 01:32:31,869
<i>they all run screaming</i>
<i>to the box office...</i>

1388
01:32:31,937 --> 01:32:34,064
and want their money back,
okay?

1389
01:32:34,139 --> 01:32:36,073
So you gotta be good!

1390
01:32:36,141 --> 01:32:38,701
- "Bach's <i>Minuet 1"?</i>
- <i>[Roberta] Yes, that's right.</i>

1391
01:32:38,777 --> 01:32:41,143
Because people are gonna be
paying good money for this concert.

1392
01:32:41,213 --> 01:32:43,238
They don't want
to hear "Twinkle."

1393
01:32:43,315 --> 01:32:48,309
Okay. [Clears Throat]
Now, on the second page of your music,
you will see a contract.

1394
01:32:48,387 --> 01:32:52,153
<i>I need you and I need your parents</i>
<i>to sign that...</i>

1395
01:32:52,224 --> 01:32:56,320
because that promises me you are gonna
be there at each and every rehearsal.

1396
01:32:56,395 --> 01:33:00,092
- Every Saturday and Sunday?
- Every Saturday and Sunday...

1397
01:33:00,165 --> 01:33:03,259
- <i>and nighttime rehearsals</i>
<i>during the week.</i>
- [Students Protesting]

1398
01:33:03,335 --> 01:33:05,269
Oh, yes!
We have six weeks, people!

1399
01:33:05,337 --> 01:33:08,363
Six weeks to this concert.
All right?

1400
01:33:08,440 --> 01:33:11,034
That's not enough time.
We can't do it all in school.

1401
01:33:11,110 --> 01:33:14,409
I'm thinking, maybe, we're gonna come
in early before school in the mornings.

1402
01:33:14,480 --> 01:33:17,938
- <i>Come in early...</i>
- [Students Groaning, Protesting]

1403
01:33:18,016 --> 01:33:20,951
No, that's what it's gonna take. Have
you ever heard of Navy SEAL training?

1404
01:33:21,019 --> 01:33:24,819
- [Students] No.
- <i>Well, this is gonna be</i>
<i>Roberta's String Training.</i>

1405
01:33:24,890 --> 01:33:28,121
- It's gonna be tough.
It's gonna be rough.
- Hi, Roberta.

1406
01:33:28,193 --> 01:33:31,026
Oh, Naeem! Oh!

1407
01:33:31,096 --> 01:33:33,428
Great!
I'm so glad you came.

1408
01:33:33,499 --> 01:33:36,093
- <i>Roberta!</i>
- Guadalupe, is that you? Oh.

1409
01:33:36,168 --> 01:33:39,137
<i>[Sighing]</i>
<i>Oh, I'm good, I'm good.</i>

1410
01:33:39,204 --> 01:33:41,138
Now, I'm grea...
That's not Lucy.

1411
01:33:41,206 --> 01:33:45,643
- [Snaps Fingers]
- Oh! Oh, guys, this is so great.

1412
01:33:45,711 --> 01:33:48,805
- And DeSean?
You're a monster. You're huge!
- How you doing?

1413
01:33:48,881 --> 01:33:52,840
[Laughing]
You grew a little.

1414
01:33:52,918 --> 01:33:55,785
You guys,
you grew a little bit.

1415
01:33:55,854 --> 01:33:59,449
Okay, these are four of my... not my
best students, but my first students.

1416
01:33:59,525 --> 01:34:05,327
- [Scoffing]
- They've agreed to come and play
in the concert with you guys.

1417
01:34:05,397 --> 01:34:08,992
I'm trying to tell them how hard
they're gonna have to work. All right?

1418
01:34:09,067 --> 01:34:12,161
<i>Take it from me,</i>
<i>you gotta work your butts off.</i>

1419
01:34:12,237 --> 01:34:14,535
<i>[Roberta]</i>
<i>Six weeks to this concert.</i>

1420
01:34:31,456 --> 01:34:33,515
- [Chuckling]
- [Exhales]

1421
01:34:33,592 --> 01:34:36,026
[Chattering]

1422
01:34:41,033 --> 01:34:43,399
Hey, Carlos, where you going?
We got a game, remember?

1423
01:34:43,468 --> 01:34:46,062
- Yeah, but I can't make it.
- What are you talking about?

1424
01:34:46,138 --> 01:34:48,197
Look, I just can't make it.

1425
01:34:48,273 --> 01:34:51,868
What? Do you have a date
with the violin teacher?

1426
01:34:51,944 --> 01:34:55,402
Yeah, I do.
Give me that.

1427
01:35:06,525 --> 01:35:08,459
More bow!

1428
01:35:09,861 --> 01:35:11,795
Stop, stop,
stop, stop, stop!

1429
01:35:11,863 --> 01:35:14,957
My God, you sound...
Is anybody practicing at all?

1430
01:35:15,033 --> 01:35:18,196
How can we practice?
We're rehearsing all the time.

1431
01:35:18,270 --> 01:35:21,706
- [Students Laughing]
- Oh, that's funny. You think
that's funny, Stephanie?

1432
01:35:21,773 --> 01:35:25,709
<i>You think the 400 people that have</i>
<i>bought tickets so far are gonna think...</i>

1433
01:35:25,777 --> 01:35:29,907
You think Itzhak Perlman is gonna
think it's funny? [Clears Throat]

1434
01:35:29,982 --> 01:35:32,212
I'm not trying
to beat you kids up.

1435
01:35:33,285 --> 01:35:35,219
I'm really not.

1436
01:35:35,287 --> 01:35:37,221
But I know two things.

1437
01:35:37,289 --> 01:35:39,553
One: If this program
disappears next year,

1438
01:35:39,625 --> 01:35:42,185
you're gonna look around, and you're
gonna really, really miss it.

1439
01:35:45,998 --> 01:35:50,901
Two: If you have
a hand in saving it,

1440
01:35:50,969 --> 01:35:53,836
<i>each one of you,</i>

1441
01:35:53,905 --> 01:35:56,203
you're gonna feel
real good.

1442
01:35:56,275 --> 01:35:58,243
Real good.

1443
01:35:58,310 --> 01:36:02,406
Boy, that will be better than any lesson
I can teach you in class.

1444
01:36:02,481 --> 01:36:07,851
It's gonna be worth it,
so please hang in there with me.

1445
01:36:08,053 --> 01:36:11,750
Oh, you know, I cannot believe
I ever agreed to do this!

1446
01:36:11,823 --> 01:36:13,688
These kids are never
gonna be ready.

1447
01:36:13,759 --> 01:36:17,354
You should hear the Bach double.
It's a complete disaster.

1448
01:36:17,429 --> 01:36:19,897
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

1449
01:36:19,965 --> 01:36:22,195
The good news is the tickets
are selling like hotcakes.

1450
01:36:22,267 --> 01:36:24,667
The bad news is the kids
sound like sh...

1451
01:36:24,736 --> 01:36:28,194
- There's more bad news.
- What?

1452
01:36:28,273 --> 01:36:31,606
- We've lost the "Y."
- What?

1453
01:36:31,677 --> 01:36:33,611
They had a flood.
A water heater burst.

1454
01:36:33,679 --> 01:36:36,876
The concert hall was damaged,
and they've canceled all events.

1455
01:36:36,948 --> 01:36:38,472
Until when?

1456
01:36:38,550 --> 01:36:41,644
- Until further notice.
- <i>Oh, no, no, no.</i>

1457
01:36:41,720 --> 01:36:45,212
This can't happen. We've sold tickets.
We've done publicity.

1458
01:36:45,290 --> 01:36:47,781
We have a concert
in three weeks.

1459
01:36:47,859 --> 01:36:51,192
I've been on the phone
all morning calling other theaters.

1460
01:36:51,263 --> 01:36:53,197
<i>Nothing's available.</i>

1461
01:36:58,503 --> 01:37:04,237
[Kids Chattering, Playing]

1462
01:37:09,981 --> 01:37:13,417
- <i>[Boy] Come on.</i>
- The teacher's late.

1463
01:37:13,485 --> 01:37:17,251
You know, I think she should
be dropped, don't you?

1464
01:37:17,322 --> 01:37:21,486
- Yeah, I don't know if we should
let her play in Fiddlefest.
- Yeah.

1465
01:37:32,537 --> 01:37:35,938
<i>[Clapping]</i>

1466
01:37:36,007 --> 01:37:39,272
Check it out.
Here you go, youngster.

1467
01:37:39,344 --> 01:37:43,041
- Yeah.
- <i>Hey, somebody gave us money!</i>

1468
01:37:43,115 --> 01:37:46,710
Stop. No, hold it.
Are you guys kidding me?

1469
01:37:46,785 --> 01:37:49,345
<i>You have</i>
<i>to have more bow.</i>

1470
01:37:49,421 --> 01:37:51,355
And you gotta go
to the frog.

1471
01:37:51,423 --> 01:37:54,551
You guys sound terrible.
I can't believe how terrible you sound.

1472
01:37:54,626 --> 01:37:58,062
- [Laughing]
- <i>You're gonna make everybody</i>
<i>sick to their stomachs.</i>

1473
01:37:58,130 --> 01:38:00,963
<i>They're gonna pay $ 1,000 a ticket,</i>
<i>and you're gonna make them throw up.</i>

1474
01:38:01,032 --> 01:38:05,128
Carlos...
you imitating me?

1475
01:38:05,203 --> 01:38:10,800
If you're imitating me, you should
do it right. Stand up straight.

1476
01:38:10,876 --> 01:38:12,969
Put that violin up.
Higher, higher.

1477
01:38:13,044 --> 01:38:14,978
Look at your feet.
All crooked.

1478
01:38:15,046 --> 01:38:17,640
Come on, continue.

1479
01:38:17,716 --> 01:38:20,082
That's okay.
You can take it from here.

1480
01:38:20,152 --> 01:38:23,588
Yeah. He's right, you know?
You do sound terrible,

1481
01:38:23,655 --> 01:38:26,715
and you are gonna make everybody sick
to their stomachs.

1482
01:38:26,792 --> 01:38:29,454
<i>Rachel! I can't believe</i>
<i>you're late. Hurry up.</i>

1483
01:38:29,528 --> 01:38:33,589
- I need to talk to you.
- All right, go on in, everybody.

1484
01:38:33,665 --> 01:38:35,963
Start on the <i>Minuet 1,</i> okay?

1485
01:38:36,034 --> 01:38:40,198
<i>I'll be there in a minute.</i>
<i>Hurry up, hurry up. Go, go, go, go, go.</i>

1486
01:38:41,973 --> 01:38:43,907
What's up?

1487
01:38:43,975 --> 01:38:46,671
We're moving away.

1488
01:38:46,745 --> 01:38:49,305
You're moving?
Where?

1489
01:38:49,381 --> 01:38:52,111
It's a secret.

1490
01:38:52,184 --> 01:38:54,277
My father...

1491
01:38:56,354 --> 01:38:59,118
has been hurting my mom.

1492
01:39:00,358 --> 01:39:02,349
So we have to get away.

1493
01:39:02,427 --> 01:39:04,759
Has he been hurting you too?

1494
01:39:08,700 --> 01:39:11,635
I'm sorry
about Juilliard...

1495
01:39:11,703 --> 01:39:14,399
and about the concert.

1496
01:39:16,942 --> 01:39:21,003
What? No. I'm not gonna take your
violin. That's yours. You keep that.

1497
01:39:21,079 --> 01:39:23,570
- No, I don't want it.
- You can't give this up.

1498
01:39:23,648 --> 01:39:26,412
It's a very
important part of you.

1499
01:39:52,244 --> 01:39:53,541
<i>[Nick]</i>
<i>Do the kids know we lost the "Y"?</i>

1500
01:39:54,813 --> 01:39:56,940
- <i>[Roberta] No.</i>
- <i>We gotta find a place.</i>

1501
01:39:57,015 --> 01:40:00,610
- <i>What about the Bronx?</i>
- <i>What about... What about Cleveland?</i>

1502
01:40:00,685 --> 01:40:02,619
We can have it
in Cleveland.

1503
01:40:02,687 --> 01:40:04,951
Mom, no one's gonna go
to the Bronx.

1504
01:40:05,023 --> 01:40:07,116
You gotta have it at one
of the schools. It'll be smaller...

1505
01:40:07,192 --> 01:40:09,217
I can't have it
at a school because...

1506
01:40:09,294 --> 01:40:11,285
- there will not be enough money raised.
- "Enough money."

1507
01:40:11,363 --> 01:40:13,558
No, because it's too small.

1508
01:40:13,632 --> 01:40:15,725
- Then just postpone it.
- I can't postpone it.

1509
01:40:15,800 --> 01:40:17,893
- Why not?
- Because Steinhardt is booked.

1510
01:40:17,969 --> 01:40:20,233
Perlman's booked
all summer long.

1511
01:40:20,305 --> 01:40:23,240
- <i>[Allegra Barking]</i>
- It's not gonna work.

1512
01:40:23,308 --> 01:40:26,038
<i>[Doorbell Rings,</i>
<i>Knocking]</i>

1513
01:40:26,111 --> 01:40:29,911
<i>[Dorothea Knocking]</i>
<i>Roberta! It's me! Are you there?</i>

1514
01:40:29,981 --> 01:40:32,609
What is she doing here?

1515
01:40:32,684 --> 01:40:37,087
Hello, hello. I have good news!
Really good news!

1516
01:40:37,155 --> 01:40:39,089
Arnold got a call from
his friend Wally Schurer...

1517
01:40:39,157 --> 01:40:41,091
who heard about us
losing the "Y,"

1518
01:40:41,159 --> 01:40:43,593
and he wanted to see
how he could help.

1519
01:40:43,662 --> 01:40:46,028
Then Wally had this brilliant idea
and called his friend Isaac Stern,

1520
01:40:46,097 --> 01:40:48,031
and it's all arranged.

1521
01:40:48,099 --> 01:40:50,033
We have a new place
for Fiddlefest.

1522
01:40:50,101 --> 01:40:52,592
- Where?
- Carnegie Hall.

1523
01:40:53,672 --> 01:40:56,266
Oh, my God!

1524
01:40:56,341 --> 01:40:58,434
[Laughing]

1525
01:40:58,510 --> 01:41:00,444
- Are you kidding me?
- No.

1526
01:41:00,512 --> 01:41:04,278
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
Oh! Oh, my...

1527
01:41:04,349 --> 01:41:07,113
<i>Isn't this terrific?</i>
<i>[Laughing]</i>

1528
01:41:07,185 --> 01:41:10,052
- It's fantastic!
- It's huge!

1529
01:41:10,121 --> 01:41:12,055
- You're a genius.
- Thank you.

1530
01:41:12,123 --> 01:41:14,057
Whoa!
That's fantastic!

1531
01:41:15,460 --> 01:41:17,553
- Oh, jeez.
- What?

1532
01:41:17,629 --> 01:41:19,563
- We can't play at Carnegie Hall.
- <i>[Nick] Mom!</i>

1533
01:41:19,631 --> 01:41:21,565
- No, I mean, you know...
- <i>[Lexi] Yeah, you can.</i>

1534
01:41:21,633 --> 01:41:24,193
- <i>[Nick] Mom.</i>
- It's fantastic.

1535
01:42:07,012 --> 01:42:09,640
<i>Amazing sound, isn't it?</i>

1536
01:42:10,749 --> 01:42:12,774
You must be Roberta.

1537
01:42:12,851 --> 01:42:15,615
- Mr. Stern.
- I was working upstairs...

1538
01:42:15,687 --> 01:42:18,383
and I thought I'd come down
and just welcome you.

1539
01:42:18,456 --> 01:42:20,890
- [Stammering]
- It's so nice to have you here
in this house.

1540
01:42:20,959 --> 01:42:24,053
Thank you very much
for your help bringing us here.

1541
01:42:24,129 --> 01:42:26,063
